      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's natural to feel that the void left by the person who loved you has irreparably changed you. It's okay to acknowledge that grief can be a deeply personal and individual experience, and there's no universal timeline for healing. Allow yourself to feel the depth of your sorrow, and don't put pressure on yourself to \"move on\" or \"get over it.\"",
      "source": "target",
